IBADAN – Oyo state government has approved March 11 as date for the inauguration of Senator Lekan Balogun as the 42nd Olubadan of Ibadan land. This was contained in a letter signed by Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Local Government and Chieftaincy Matters, Dr Bashir Olanrewaju. The letter was addressed to Senator Lekan Balogun, titled: “Installation Ceremony: Olubadan of Ibadan’, affirmed the governor’s approval. Ogun SSG Visits Orimolusi Of Ijebu-Igbo Ahead Of Coronation Ogun Govt Approves Adebajo’s Appointment As Orimolusi Of… The letter reads: “I wish to refer to a letter No.18SELG.243TI/17 of 16 February, 2022 on the above subject and inform you that His Excellency, the Executive Governor of Oyo State has approved Friday, 11 of March, 2022 as the date of the Installation of the New Olubadan of Ibadan. Once again, Congratulations, Kabiyesi.” Makinde had on February 14 approved Balogun’s emergence following a recommendation to that effect by the Olubadan-in-Council which was communicated to the governor.